-- Danone, Ferragamo, Villeroy: European Equity Preview
-- B y   J o s e p h   C i o l l i
-- 2012-03-16T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-15/danone-ferragamo-villeroy-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  (SXXP) trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index (SXXP)  rose 0.3 percent to 270.98. The
 Stoxx 50 Index (SX5P)  (SX5P) increased 0.2 percent to 2,538.98. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, gained
0.7 percent to 2,593.97.  Credit Agricole SA (ACA)  : The France bank’s agreement to
buy back subordinated debt at its Emporiki Bank in  Greece  will
result in a profit of 550 million euros ($720 million). The bank
also said it will write down 130 million euros in Emporiki
deferred tax assets and take a charge on the Greek unit’s risk.
The shares rose 1 percent to 5.12 euros.  Danone SA (BN)  : The world’s largest yogurt maker was
lowered to hold from buy at Hamburger Sparkasse. The shares
dropped 0.3 percent to 52.74 euros.  Salvatore Ferragamo SpA (SFER)  (SFER IM): The Italian clothing and
accessories company forecast “significant” growth in 2012
after reporting earnings before interest and taxes of 156.6
million euros, beating the average analyst estimate of 152.5
million euros. The shares fell 1.6 percent to 15.20 euros.  Villeroy & Boch AG (VIB3)  (VIB3 GY): The German tile and porcelain
maker said it’s proposing a dividend of 35 euro cents per
ordinary share for 2011, up from 15 euro cents in 2010, and of
40 euro cents per preferred share, compared with 20 euro cents a
year earlier. The shares gained 3 percent to 7.41 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
